        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Currency comparison methods are comparing floating point values instead of monetary values.\r\nI think that makes those methods unusable because in practice people only want to compare fixed\r\nprecision numbers when they deal with currency.\r\n\r\ne.g\r\nwhen I'm working with 2 digit precision I want $1.01 to be same when compared to 1.010101\r\n\r\nWhile this is not a bug, I still feel it's not the right way to do it."
        },
